a simple challenge, we are provided with the clue in the challenege description itself 

Description
A type of transposition cipher is the rail fence cipher, which is described here. Here is one such cipher encrypted using the rail fence with 4 rails. Can you decrypt it? Download the message here. Put the decoded message in the picoCTF flag format, 

so i opened up dcode.fr and entered the encrypted text from the attachement of the challenge 

and analyzed the cipher and chose the 
rail fence cipher 

and pasted the excrypted text there 

there i enabled the "keep punctuations and spaces" option

then selected the from "from top" 

and entered the number of rows and column as 4

and give decrypt 

this gives us the flag content, then we paste the content in the flag format 

